title: What can I do if my phone does not have sufficient storage?
answer:
l   If you have inserted a microSD card into your phone, move your photos, songs, videos, and other files to the microSD card.

![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141208145320998001.jpg)![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141208145321754002.jpg)![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141208145321293003.jpg)  

l   Clean your phone storage: On the **Phone Manager** screen, touch **Phone accelerator** > **Storage cleaner** > **Smart scan**, and follow the onscreen instructions to perform a smart scan, and clear the application cache, system trash files, applications you no longer need and their installation packages, and large files, such as videos and compressed packages.

![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141208145322354004.jpg)![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141208145322264005.jpg)

If the problem persists, back up important data and restore your phone to its factory settings.

![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141208145323490006.png)

The figures are for your reference only. The actual screens may vary.
